(130, 1, '2017-10-05 05:54:23', '2017-10-05 05:54:23', '', 'JudsonIvy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'judsonivy', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:54:23', '2017-10-05 05:54:23', '', 128, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//wp-content/uploads/2017/10/JudsonIvy.vcf', 0, 'attachment', 'text/x-vcard', 0),
(131, 1, '2017-10-05 05:55:38', '2017-10-05 05:55:38', 'John is a seasoned healthcare finance executive with more than 20 years experience in roles ranging from hospital CFO to Vice President of Operations for a 71 hospital system. John brings an extensive background in corporate finance, treasury, financial planning and analysis, tax, strategic planning and risk management along with a deep appreciation for revenue cycle management.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Ensemble, John served for two years as VP of Finance at Angel Medflight. From 1999 through 2014 John worked for Health Management Associates (HMA).  While at HMA, he served in a variety of roles, including stints as CFO in several hospitals, until ultimately being tapped to be Vice President of Financial Operations at the Corporate Office. John holds a B.S. in Accounting from the University of Memphis.', 'John Erickson', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-erickson', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:55:38', '2017-10-05 05:55:38', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=team&#038;p=131', 0, 'team', '', 0),
(132, 1, '2017-10-05 05:55:28', '2017-10-05 05:55:28', '', 'john-erickson_2_2076926781', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'john-erickson_2_2076926781', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:55:28', '2017-10-05 05:55:28', '', 131, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//wp-content/uploads/2017/10/john-erickson_2_2076926781.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(133, 1, '2017-10-05 05:56:19', '2017-10-05 05:56:19', 'Shannon White is a senior revenue cycle operations and business development executive with over 25 years of healthcare experience and a proven history of building successful teams and implementing strategies that improve financial performance. She is an effective leader who can coach, motivate and leverage relationships to inspire vision and success.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Ensemble, Shannon served as Vice President of the Shared Services Center for Fort Smith, LLC, a subsidiary of Community Health Systems. She managed the growth of the Service Center from a standalone business office to over 50 facilities operating in nine states. Working with the governor of Arkansas, she negotiated $22 million in rebate programs and economic development incentives for the organization. Under her leadership, her team grew to more than 700 team members. Within Fort Smith, this growth was a tremendous accomplishment and reflective of her organization becom¬≠ing the employer of choice. Through various cost savings initiatives and efficiency, she improved cost to collect, year over year. She also maintained a cash collection to net revenue percentage of 103% or above annually and led a reduc¬≠tion of net AR days to 53.\r\n\r\nShannon is known for her visionary leadership, high performance, and creating a successful culture of servant leadership.', 'Shannon White', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shannon-white', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:56:19', '2017-10-05 05:56:19', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=team&#038;p=133', 0, 'team', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2017-10-05 05:56:08', '2017-10-05 05:56:08', '', 'Shannon_White', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'shannon_white', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:56:08', '2017-10-05 05:56:08', '', 133, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Shannon_White.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(135, 1, '2017-10-05 05:57:03', '2017-10-05 05:57:03', 'Estelle contributes her expertise, strategy and experience in results driven client service excellence at Ensemble Health Partners. Estelle brings 25 years of healthcare revenue cycle delivery experience, and specializes in client relationship management and strategic account development. Her varied experience in hospital, physician and vendor partnership work adds a strong focus on the development and management of world-class relationships with new and existing customers. \r\nA respected speaker and contributor, Estelle has held various leadership roles within HFMA and will serve as President of the South Carolina Chapter (2016-2017). She also serves as a founding member of the HFMA HERE national advisory board, focused on curriculum for the development of women in healthcare leadership. She is also an Advisory Board Member for Ashford University (CA), and a member of ACHE.', 'Estelle Barnes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'estelle-barnes', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:57:03', '2017-10-05 05:57:03', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=team&#038;p=135', 0, 'team', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2017-10-05 05:56:46', '2017-10-05 05:56:46', '', 'img_thumb_barnes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'img_thumb_barnes', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:56:46', '2017-10-05 05:56:46', '', 135, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_thumb_barnes.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(137, 1, '2017-10-05 05:58:05', '2017-10-05 05:58:05', 'In his role at Ensemble Health Partners, Sean focuses on helping clients ensure accurate charge capture, effective financial counseling and third party eligibility screening processes, effective DNFB management, and best practice patient access operations. He has served as business office director, corporate director of revenue cycle and most recently, regional director of patient access for 22 hospitals at Health Management Associates. Among his credits, Sean was responsible for achieving the lowest DNFB days and for increasing point-of-service collections by the highest percentage among 70 hospitals. Ensemble Health Partners‚Äô clients benefit from Sean''s ability to think and operate at both the strategic and granular levels to ensure success.', 'Sean Hayes CRCR, MBA, CRCS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sean-hayes-crcr-mba-crcs', '', '', '2017-10-05 05:58:05', '2017-10-05 05:58:05', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=team&#038;p=137', 0, 'team', '', 0),
