(189, 1, '2017-10-05 07:59:31', '2017-10-05 07:59:31', 'Payers are sizing up ledger tech for payments and claims processing, but one big area of growth could be next-generation personal health records.', 'Blockchain Eyed For Potential Use Cases in Revenue Cycle', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'blockchain-eyed-for-potential-use-cases-in-revenue-cycle', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:39', '2017-10-05 09:55:39', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=189', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(190, 1, '2017-10-05 07:59:53', '2017-10-05 07:59:53', 'U.S News &amp; World Report will delay the release of its 2017-18 Best Hospitals rankings to Aug. 8 after researchers discovered errors in the data used to compile the rankings. The rankings were to be published Aug. 1. However, researchers uncovered errors requiring the rankings to be reassessed, officials said in a statement on the publication''s website.', 'US News Delays Hospital Rankings to Fix Data Problems', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'us-news-delays-hospital-rankings-to-fix-data-problems', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:28', '2017-10-05 09:55:28', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=190', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(191, 1, '2017-10-05 08:00:13', '2017-10-05 08:00:13', 'Hospital cost-cutting and competition have caused healthcare prices to slip to their lowest rate of growth in a year, according to a new report from the Altarum Institute.', 'Healthcare Pricing Falls to Lowest Growth Rate in a Year', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthcare-pricing-falls-to-lowest-growth-rate-in-a-year', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:20', '2017-10-05 09:55:20', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=191', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(192, 1, '2017-10-05 08:00:35', '2017-10-05 08:00:35', 'Hailed as one of the primary vehicles for driving the industry away from fee-for-service arrangements, accountable care organizations now cover roughly 10% of the U.S. population, according to Leavitt Partners and the Accountable Care Learning Collaborative. The groups found that 923 public and private ACOs were operating nationwide as of March 31.', 'Data Points: ACOs Keep Evolving, Now Covering 10% of U.S. Population', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'data-points-acos-keep-evolving-now-covering-10-of-u-s-population', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:12', '2017-10-05 09:55:12', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=192', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(193, 1, '2017-10-05 08:00:58', '2017-10-05 08:00:58', 'The majority of C-suite executives (85 percent) agree cyberattacks will become more frequent and more costly, according to a global survey by the management consulting firm A.T. Kearney.', '43% of C-Suite Execs Name Cybersecurity as No. 1 Operational Challenge', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '43-of-c-suite-execs-name-cybersecurity-as-no-1-operational-challenge', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:02', '2017-10-05 09:55:02', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=193', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(194, 1, '2017-10-05 08:01:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Auto Draft', '', 'auto-draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:01:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&p=194', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(195, 1, '2017-10-05 08:01:27', '2017-10-05 08:01:27', 'Hospital borrowing has the debt markets booming.Whether that''s the case a year from now is anyone''s guess. Although efforts to replace elements of the Affordable Care Act will likely come to a head this week, 2018 won''t be without its share of uncertainty.', 'Hospitals Handling Growing Debt Loads ‚Äî For Now', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospitals-handling-growing-debt-loads-for-now', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:54:53', '2017-10-05 09:54:53', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=195', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(196, 1, '2017-10-05 08:01:48', '2017-10-05 08:01:48', 'Hospitals cited "reviewing and optimizing current operational and clinical processes" as their top strategy for containing costs in the next three years, according to a survey of U.S. hospital executives. The survey, conducted by Economist Intelligence Unit and sponsored by Prudential Retirement, took place last January and February. More than 300 hospital executives participated.', '300+ Hospital Executives Tell Their No. 1 Financial Strategy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-hospital-executives-tell-their-no-1-financial-strategy', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:56:06', '2017-10-05 09:56:06', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=196', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(197, 1, '2017-10-05 08:02:10', '2017-10-05 08:02:10', 'Ascension''s advertising has taken a decidedly digital turn as the Catholic giant rebrands all of its facilities. St. Louis-based Ascension joins many other health systems that are moving more of their marketing budgets to digital and away from traditional media because that''s where consumers are going first to research their conditions and providers, marketing executives say.', 'Hospitals Work to Harness the Power of Digital Marketing', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospitals-work-to-harness-the-power-of-digital-marketing', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:56:02', '2017-10-05 09:56:02', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=197', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2017-10-05 08:02:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Auto Draft', '', 'auto-draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:02:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&p=198', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(199, 1, '2017-10-05 08:02:39', '2017-10-05 08:02:39', 'It seems hospitals and health systems are pretty good places to work. That''s one of the takeaways from Forbes'' annual list of America''s Best Employers, as healthcare organizations nabbed 25 out of the top 100 slots in the large employer category - a full 25 percent, better than the other industries that were represented on the list.', 'Healthcare Providers Make Up Big Slice of Forbes ''Best Employers'' List', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthcare-providers-make-up-big-slice-of-forbes-best-employers-list', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:01:37', '2017-10-05 10:01:37', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=199', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(200, 1, '2017-10-05 08:02:58', '2017-10-05 08:02:58', '‚ÄúU up?‚Äù No, it''s not a text from a paramour. Instead, it''s the opening line from one of Healthgrades'' chatbots. They conduct automated conversations with patients, checking in about their health in between physician appointments.', 'Engaging With Patients to Keep Them Happy and Healthy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'engaging-with-patients-to-keep-them-happy-and-healthy', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:01:24', '2017-10-05 10:01:24', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=200', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(201, 1, '2017-10-05 08:03:16', '2017-10-05 08:03:16', 'The Department of Veterans Affairs is considering closing over 1,165 of its facilities as part of its plans to let more veterans receive medical care in the private sector, VA Secretary David Shulkin, MD, told U.S. House of Representatives Committee on Appropriations on Wednesday.', 'VA May Close 1,100 Facilities to Privatize More Veterans Healthcare', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'va-may-close-1100-facilities-to-privatize-more-veterans-healthcare', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:01:12', '2017-10-05 10:01:12', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=201', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(202, 1, '2017-10-05 08:03:34', '2017-10-05 08:03:34', 'Since its implementation in 2010, evidence shows the Hospital Readmission Reduction Program cut reduced hospital readmissions for certain conditions, as was the program''s intent. A new Health Affairs study, however, indicates the current penalty structure leads some hospitals to be penalized persistently, leading to a financial burden.', 'Despite Cutting Readmissions, HRRP Penalties Hit Some Hospitals More', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'despite-cutting-readmissions-hrrp-penalties-hit-some-hospitals-more', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:01:01', '2017-10-05 10:01:01', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=202', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(203, 1, '2017-10-05 08:03:58', '2017-10-05 08:03:58', 'A hospital bill can be a complicated endeavor for a patient, prompting a backlash if it''s not easily decodable. Recently, four hospital systems in Colorado - Centura Health, Health One, SCL Health and UCHealth - found themselves on the defensive after 9News, based in Kusa, ran a piece that was critical of their billing practices.', 'As Patients Take Hospital Bill Issues Public, Hospitals Take Stock of Their Practices', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'as-patients-take-hospital-bill-issues-public-hospitals-take-stock-of-their-practices', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:00:53', '2017-10-05 10:00:53', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=203', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(204, 1, '2017-10-05 08:04:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Auto Draft', '', 'auto-draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:04:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&p=204', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(205, 1, '2017-10-05 08:04:23', '2017-10-05 08:04:23', 'Kim Dearnley couldn''t call in sick after waking up recently with a sore throat.As a computer trainer, she had limited sick days.So she turned instead to the internet, where she found that the wait time was just 20 minutes at an Advocate Clinic at a Walgreens in her Chicago neighborhood.', 'Providers Confront Growing Demand For Instant Access', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'providers-confront-growing-demand-for-instant-access', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:00:43', '2017-10-05 10:00:43', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=205', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(206, 1, '2017-10-05 08:04:44', '2017-10-05 08:04:44', 'The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services has issued the final market stabilization rule for insurers in the Affordable Care Act market that includes a shortening the open enrollment period for 2018. Also, for the 2018 plan year and beyond, the final rule gives issuers greater benefit design in allowing additional actuarial value flexibility to develop more choices with lower premium options for consumers, CMS said.', 'CMS Final Rule Gives Insurers Greater Options for Benefit Design on Obamacare Exchanges', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-final-rule-gives-insurers-greater-options-for-benefit-design-on-obamacare-exchanges', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:00:33', '2017-10-05 10:00:33', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=206', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(207, 1, '2017-10-05 08:05:03', '2017-10-05 08:05:03', 'As the healthcare industry continues it''s slow but sure transition to value-based care, the positive effect this may have on hospitals is emerging, with those taking part in one or more value-based programs showing lower readmission rates and bigger cost savings, according to the Journal of the American Medical Association.', 'Value-Based Programs Yield Lower Readmission Rates, Significant Cost Savings, JAMA Study Shows', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'value-based-programs-yield-lower-readmission-rates-significant-cost-savings-jama-study-shows', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:00:15', '2017-10-05 10:00:15', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=207', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(208, 1, '2017-10-05 08:05:27', '2017-10-05 08:05:27', 'The Leapfrog Group on Wednesday released its Spring 2017 Hospital Safety Grade, highlighting hundreds of hospitals that are leading in preventing deadly medical errors at their facilities. The Leapfrog Hospital Safety Grade, the first and only national healthcare rating focused on errors, accidents and infections, assigns A through F letter grades to general acute-care hospitals.', 'Leapfrog Releases Hospital Safety Grades, Says 1,000 Patients a Day Still Killed by Medical Errors', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leapfrog-releases-hospital-safety-grades-says-1000-patients-a-day-still-killed-by-medical-errors', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:00:03', '2017-10-05 10:00:03', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=208', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(209, 1, '2017-10-05 08:05:45', '2017-10-05 08:05:45', 'The number of Americans without health insurance swelled to 11.3 percent during the first quarter 2017, compared to 10.9 percent in the third and fourth quarters of 2016, according to a Gallup-Healthways poll. The 11.3 percent represents a record low since Gallup and population health company Healthways began tracking insurance coverage in 2008.', 'Uninsured Rate Swells to 11.3% in First Quarter 2017 After Record Low', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'uninsured-rate-swells-to-11-3-in-first-quarter-2017-after-record-low', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:59:46', '2017-10-05 09:59:46', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=209', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2017-10-05 08:06:08', '2017-10-05 08:06:08', 'The CMS has sent a rule designed to stabilize the individual health insurance market to the Office of Management and Budget for final review. The Trump administration hopes to finalize the rule very soon.', 'CMS Readies Insurance Market Stabilization Rule as Insurers Wait Nervously', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-readies-insurance-market-stabilization-rule-as-insurers-wait-nervously', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:59:25', '2017-10-05 09:59:25', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=210', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(211, 1, '2017-10-05 08:06:28', '2017-10-05 08:06:28', 'Commercial plans are following Medicare''s lead, but physicians need more flexibility, experts say.', 'As Payers See Success in Bundled Payments, Critics Say Model Needs Fine-Tuning', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'as-payers-see-success-in-bundled-payments-critics-say-model-needs-fine-tuning', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:59:15', '2017-10-05 09:59:15', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=211', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2017-10-05 08:06:54', '2017-10-05 08:06:54', 'Almost one in four non-elderly Americans had medical debt past-due in 2015, and it was more common in states with high rates of uninsured people, according to a recent study conducted by the Urban Institute.', '10 States With the Highest Rates of Past-Due Medical Debt in 2015', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-states-with-the-highest-rates-of-past-due-medical-debt-in-2015', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:59:00', '2017-10-05 09:59:00', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=212', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2017-10-05 08:07:15', '2017-10-05 08:07:15', 'Even if the Affordable Care Act were to remain intact, upwards of 670 rural hospitals across the country are at risk of shutting their doors, according to findings from iVantage Health Analytics. But with the federal health law threatened by Republican majorities in Congress, thin margins will likely turn into losses.', 'Hundreds of Rural Hospitals Already at Risk of Closing as ACA Repeal Looms, Increasing Their Vulnerability', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hundreds-of-rural-hospitals-already-at-risk-of-closing-as-aca-repeal-looms-increasing-their-vulnerability', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:58:49', '2017-10-05 09:58:49', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=213', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2017-10-05 08:07:35', '2017-10-05 08:07:35', 'Healthgrades has released its list of America''s 50 and 100 Best Hospitals for 2017 for demonstrating what the organization calls "superior clinical outcomes" across the majority of common inpatient conditions and procedures for at least three consecutive years.', 'Healthgrades Names 100 Top Hospitals For 2017; See the List', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthgrades-names-100-top-hospitals-for-2017-see-the-list', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:58:38', '2017-10-05 09:58:38', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=214', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(215, 1, '2017-10-05 08:07:54', '2017-10-05 08:07:54', 'Is the U.S. healthcare industry thinking about value-based care the right way? No, or at least, not yet, suggested a panel of executives at Columbia Business School''s annual healthcare conference in New York City Friday.', 'Vital Signs: Does the U.S. Have the Right Mindset For Value-Based Care?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vital-signs-does-the-u-s-have-the-right-mindset-for-value-based-care', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:58:27', '2017-10-05 09:58:27', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=215', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(216, 1, '2017-10-05 08:08:12', '2017-10-05 08:08:12', 'Proposed rate changes to Medicare Advantage rates in 2018 would result in an estimated 2 percent reduction in MA insurer net revenues, which could mean cuts to beneficiary coverage and benefits, according to a Feb. 22 report by Oliver Wyman, sponsored by America''s Health Insurance plans.', 'Healthcare Costs Will Outpace Medicare Advantage Payments in 2018, Report Says', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthcare-costs-will-outpace-medicare-advantage-payments-in-2018-report-says', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:58:17', '2017-10-05 09:58:17', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=216', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(217, 1, '2017-10-05 08:08:31', '2017-10-05 08:08:31', 'New estimates released Wednesday from the Office of the Actuary at the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services project an average rate of national health spending growth of 5.6 percent for 2016 to 2025, outpacing the average projected growth in gross domestic product by 1.2 percent.', 'CMS: Health Spending Growth Will Outpace Projected Growth in GDP', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-health-spending-growth-will-outpace-projected-growth-in-gdp', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:58:08', '2017-10-05 09:58:08', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=217', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(218, 1, '2017-10-05 08:08:49', '2017-10-05 08:08:49', 'New survey data from the American Hospital Association underscore the wide variation in hospital expenses from state to state and between different types of facilities. Adjusted expenses per inpatient day in 2015 were highest at not-for-profit hospitals, at $2,413, and lowest at for-profit hospitals, at $1,831, according the AHA''s latest annual survey.', 'AHA Survey Shows Variation in Hospital Expenses', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'aha-survey-shows-variation-in-hospital-expenses', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:57:53', '2017-10-05 09:57:53', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=218', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(219, 1, '2017-10-05 08:09:08', '2017-10-05 08:09:08', 'When it comes to the biggest challenges facing revenue cycle professionals, the new role patients have in paying for the cost of care is one of the most pressing.', 'Revenue Cycle Departments Must Be More Patient-Centered to Succeed, Experts Say', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-cycle-departments-must-be-more-patient-centered-to-succeed-experts-say', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:57:39', '2017-10-05 09:57:39', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=219', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2017-10-05 08:09:23', '2017-10-05 08:09:23', 'President Donald Trump''s executive order Friday evening instructing federal agencies to go as far as they legally can to roll back the Affordable Care Act was not exactly surprising. But the order - along with Trump senior advisor Kellyanne Conway''s statement Sunday that Trump may stop enforcing the law''s tax penalty against people who don''t buy insurance - has rattled insurers and health policy experts.', 'Trump''s ACA Executive Order Heightens Insurance Market Jitters', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'trumps-aca-executive-order-heightens-insurance-market-jitters', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:09:31', '2017-10-05 08:09:31', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=220', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(221, 1, '2017-10-05 08:09:56', '2017-10-05 08:09:56', 'Late last year, Quest Diagnostics disclosed that hackers infiltrated its patient portal, gaining access to names, dates of birth, telephone numbers and lab results. The frequency and scope of data breaches - from cyberattacks to simple theft and loss - has grown along with the exploding volume of digitalized information in healthcare delivery and financial transactions.', 'Data Points: Healthcare Data Breaches', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'data-points-healthcare-data-breaches', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:09:56', '2017-10-05 08:09:56', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=221', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(222, 1, '2017-10-05 08:12:27', '2017-10-05 08:12:27', 'The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services has announced 45 providers that are participating in the Next Generation accountable care organization model, up from an estimated 17 the year before.', 'CMS Announces 45 ACOs Are Now Participating in Next Generation Model', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-announces-45-acos-are-now-participating-in-next-generation-model', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:12:28', '2017-10-05 08:12:28', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=222', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(223, 1, '2017-10-05 08:12:50', '2017-10-05 08:12:50', 'Hospital and health system partnership and merger transaction continue an overall uptick, jumping 55 percent from 66 announced in 2010 to 102 in 2016, management and consulting firm Kaufman Hall said in an analysis released earlier this week.', 'Upward Trend in Merger, Acquisition Activity Continues With Nonprofits Leading the Charge', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'upward-trend-in-merger-acquisition-activity-continues-with-nonprofits-leading-the-charge', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:12:50', '2017-10-05 08:12:50', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=223', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2017-10-05 08:13:12', '2017-10-05 08:13:12', 'A mere two days before leaving Washington, officials at the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services touted gains in alternative payment models that have resulted in more than 359,000 clinicians confirmed to participate in four of the agency''s top APMs in 2017. CMS called it ''an important part of the Administration''s effort to build a system that delivers better care and one in which clinicians work together to have a full understanding of patients'' needs.', 'CMS: More Than 359,000 Clinicians to Participate in Top APMs in 2017', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-more-than-359000-clinicians-to-participate-in-top-apms-in-2017', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:13:12', '2017-10-05 08:13:12', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=224', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(225, 1, '2017-10-05 08:13:38', '2017-10-05 08:13:38', 'The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services has extended the deadline for hospitals to submit electronic clinical quality measure data for the 2016 reporting period. The eCQM reporting is to determine payment for 2018.', 'CMS Extends Hospital eCQM Reporting Deadline', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-extends-hospital-ecqm-reporting-deadline', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:13:38', '2017-10-05 08:13:38', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=225', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(226, 1, '2017-10-05 08:42:10', '2017-10-05 08:42:10', 'House members voted 227 to 198 on Friday to advance repeal of the Affordable Care Act in a budget resolution bill. The budget will allow Republicans to pass any repeal and replacement of ACA with a simple majority vote in a procedural tool known as reconciliation.', 'House Advances ACA Repeal In Budget Resolution', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'house-advances-aca-repeal-in-budget-resolution', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:42:10', '2017-10-05 08:42:10', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=226', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(227, 1, '2017-10-05 08:42:35', '2017-10-05 08:42:35', 'In 2012, Medicare began using a new tactic to get hospitals to reduce costly, unnecessary readmissions: It fined them. The Hospital Readmissions Reduction Program, established in the 2010 Affordable Care Act, allows the CMS to withhold inpatient prospective payments to short-term acute hospitals with excessive readmissions for certain conditions.', 'Study Finds CMS'' Hospital Readmission Penalties Worked Under Affordable Care Act', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'study-finds-cms-hospital-readmission-penalties-worked-under-affordable-care-act', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:42:35', '2017-10-05 08:42:35', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=227', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(228, 1, '2017-10-05 08:42:54', '2017-10-05 08:42:54', 'A federal judge dismissed a class action against Blue Shield Life &amp; Health and Blue Shield of California alleging the insurers unfairly denied patients coverage for the expensive hepatitis C drug Harvoni.', 'Judge Drops Blue Shield of California Class-Action Suit Over Hep C Drug Denials', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'judge-drops-blue-shield-of-california-class-action-suit-over-hep-c-drug-denials', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:42:54', '2017-10-05 08:42:54', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=228', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2017-10-05 08:43:12', '2017-10-05 08:43:12', 'More than 1 in 4 adults younger than 65 live with conditions that private insurers could have declined to cover in some policies prior to the Affordable Care Act, according to an analysis by the Kaiser Family Foundation.', '52 Million People With Pre-Existing Conditions Could Be Denied Coverage If Obamacare Provision Is Dropped', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-million-people-with-pre-existing-conditions-could-be-denied-coverage-if-obamacare-provision-is-dropped', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:43:12', '2017-10-05 08:43:12', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=229', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(230, 1, '2017-10-05 08:43:30', '2017-10-05 08:43:30', 'As the role of the hospital chief financial officer changes to adapt to reimbursement changes in healthcare, a new survey found 91 percent of global CFOs and senior finance professionals think their organization should be doing more with data to inform their strategic decisions.', 'Hospital CFOs Should Be More Nimble, Leverage Technology, Says Kaufman Hall', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospital-cfos-should-be-more-nimble-leverage-technology-says-kaufman-hall', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:43:30', '2017-10-05 08:43:30', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=230', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(231, 1, '2017-10-05 08:43:46', '2017-10-05 08:43:46', 'The U.S. House of Representatives passed omnibus healthcare legislation Wednesday that would preserve payment rates for more off-campus hospital outpatient departments, among other provisions sought by hospitals.', 'House Passes Healthcare Bill With HOPD Provisions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'house-passes-healthcare-bill-with-hopd-provisions', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:43:46', '2017-10-05 08:43:46', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=231', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(232, 1, '2017-10-05 08:44:05', '2017-10-05 08:44:05', 'A national chief information security officer could help stem the flood of data breaches hitting the healthcare industry, according to the country''s largest healthcare IT industry trade association.', 'HIMSS Says Federal Government Needs a National Chief Information Security Officer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'himss-says-federal-government-needs-a-national-chief-information-security-officer', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:44:05', '2017-10-05 08:44:05', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=232', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(233, 1, '2017-10-05 08:44:23', '2017-10-05 08:44:23', 'One-third of Medicare beneficiaries will see a 10 percent Part B premium increase next year - less than originally projected because of intervention from federal health officials.', 'HHS Taps Reserves to Ease Projected Part B Premium Rise', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hhs-taps-reserves-to-ease-projected-part-b-premium-rise', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:44:23', '2017-10-05 08:44:23', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=233', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(234, 1, '2017-10-05 08:45:09', '2017-10-05 08:45:09', 'Although the CMS relaxed some controversial provisions in its final rule on how off-campus facilities will be reimbursed by Medicare, experts say the change will still put pressure on hospitals'' relationships with commercial payers and prevent them from bringing care closer to patients.', 'Site-Neutral Pay Rule Leaves Hospital-Owned Outpatient Facilities With Uncertain Future', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'site-neutral-pay-rule-leaves-hospital-owned-outpatient-facilities-with-uncertain-future', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:45:09', '2017-10-05 08:45:09', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=234', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(235, 1, '2017-10-05 08:45:35', '2017-10-05 08:45:35', 'Health insurance premiums for the benchmark exchange plans are set to rise 25% on average in 2017. But policy experts say the projected double-digit hikes are unlikely to affect the majority of people who enroll in health plans through the federal exchange.', 'Double-Digit Premium Hikes Unlikely to Affect Most ACA Shoppers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'double-digit-premium-hikes-unlikely-to-affect-most-aca-shoppers', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:45:35', '2017-10-05 08:45:35', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=235', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(236, 1, '2017-10-05 08:45:55', '2017-10-05 08:45:55', 'A new Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services review revealed at a recent industry conference found that almost 46 percent of the 5,832 doctors listed in 54 private MA plans provided wrong information, limiting beneficiaries‚Äô ability to get needed care.', 'Errors Plague Medicare Advantage Provider Directories', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'errors-plague-medicare-advantage-provider-directories', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:45:55', '2017-10-05 08:45:55', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=236', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(237, 1, '2017-10-05 08:46:11', '2017-10-05 08:46:11', 'Healthgrades published its ratings of hospitals across the country, and also launched its Risk IQ Tool to help consumers assess their personal risk to six common surgical procedures. See the top 50 hospitals that Healthgrades ranked based solely on clinical outcomes.', 'Healthgrades 2017 Report Ranks Top Hospitals', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthgrades-2017-report-ranks-top-hospitals', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:46:11', '2017-10-05 08:46:11', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=237', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(238, 1, '2017-10-05 08:46:29', '2017-10-05 08:46:29', 'The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services on Friday released the final version of its physician Quality Payment Program under MACRA that it said adds flexibility like 90-day reporting to the program to overhaul how physicians are paid under Medicare.', 'CMS Releases MACRA Final Rule, Makes 2017 ''Transition Year,'' Adds 90-Day Reporting Option', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-releases-macra-final-rule-makes-2017-transition-year-adds-90-day-reporting-option', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:46:29', '2017-10-05 08:46:29', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=238', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(239, 1, '2017-10-05 08:46:49', '2017-10-05 08:46:49', 'The shift from volume to value; wellness and health management; system decentralization; technological advances and digitization; and consumerism are the five biggest forces driving change in the U.S. healthcare industry, according to new findings from PricewaterhouseCooper''s Health Research Institute.', 'Value-Based Pay, Wellness, Retail Clinics Among 5 Top Forces Reshaping Healthcare, PricewaterhouseCoopers Says', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'value-based-pay-wellness-retail-clinics-among-5-top-forces-reshaping-healthcare-pricewaterhousecoopers-says', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:46:49', '2017-10-05 08:46:49', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=239', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(240, 1, '2017-10-05 08:47:05', '2017-10-05 08:47:05', 'The U.S. uninsured rate fell to another historic low in 2015, and premiums for employer-based plans barely budged in 2016. But those positive insurance numbers mask the fact that more Americans are becoming ‚Äúunderinsured‚Äù and face higher out-of-pocket obligations.', 'More Americans Gain Health Coverage, But Their Cost-Sharing Keeps Rising', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'more-americans-gain-health-coverage-but-their-cost-sharing-keeps-rising', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:47:05', '2017-10-05 08:47:05', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=240', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2017-10-05 08:47:21', '2017-10-05 08:47:21', 'More hospital and health systems are turning their attention to their revenue cycle''s mid-cycle operations as cost pressures force providers to shore up areas where systems are losing money.', 'Mid-Cycle Losses Have Healthcare Focusing on Coding, Predictive Analytics to Improve Revenue Cycle', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mid-cycle-losses-have-healthcare-focusing-on-coding-predictive-analytics-to-improve-revenue-cycle', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:47:21', '2017-10-05 08:47:21', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=241', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(242, 1, '2017-10-05 08:47:41', '2017-10-05 08:47:41', 'Newly released Medicare data may not provide much help to the 800 hospitals subject to the first mandatory payment bundle, industry watchers say. But that doesn‚Äôt mean those hospitals should be sitting still.', 'Hospitals May Not Get Clear Answers From Early CJR Data', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospitals-may-not-get-clear-answers-from-early-cjr-data', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:47:41', '2017-10-05 08:47:41', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=242', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(243, 1, '2017-10-05 08:47:58', '2017-10-05 08:47:58', 'The CMS has issued an 11-page list of questions and answers to better guide providers in using ICD-10 codes. The federally mandated conversion to the more numerous and granular ICD-10 family of diagnostic and procedural codes began Oct. 1, 2015, but not before the American Medical Association and other groups extracted concessions from the CMS.', 'Get Ready For the End of ICD-10 ''Flexibilities''', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'get-ready-for-the-end-of-icd-10-flexibilities', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:47:58', '2017-10-05 08:47:58', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=243', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(244, 1, '2017-10-05 08:48:21', '2017-10-05 08:48:21', 'Locky ransomware is back in the spotlight, after FireEye Labs, a cybersecurity and malware protection provider, observed the virus has evolved and is targeting hospitals with a massive campaign.', 'Locky Ransomware Attacks Hit Hospitals the Hardest, Report says', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'locky-ransomware-attacks-hit-hospitals-the-hardest-report-says', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:48:21', '2017-10-05 08:48:21', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=244', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2017-10-05 08:48:39', '2017-10-05 08:48:39', 'More than half of U.S. hospitals will be penalized in fiscal 2017 for having readmission rates higher than the acceptable level set by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services. And for many of them, the latest payment reduction marks the 5th year in a row that CMS has adjusted the rates based on their readmissions.', 'See Which Hospitals Will Pay Readmission Fines in 2017', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'see-which-hospitals-will-pay-readmission-fines-in-2017', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:48:39', '2017-10-05 08:48:39', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=245', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(246, 1, '2017-10-05 08:48:56', '2017-10-05 08:48:56', 'The CMS announced a proposal last week to put three new episodes of care under mandatory experiments with bundled payments, potentially compelling hundreds of additional hospitals into becoming financially accountable for what happens to Medicare patients long after they leave the hospital.', 'Bundled-Payment Expansion Brings Providers More Risk‚Äîand Opportunity', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bundled-payment-expansion-brings-providers-more-risk-and-opportunity', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:48:56', '2017-10-05 08:48:56', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=246', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(247, 1, '2017-10-05 08:49:13', '2017-10-05 08:49:13', 'The majority of states could be doing more to make price transparency the norm and enable educated healthcare choices for consumers, according to a joint report from the Health Care Incentives Improvement Institute and Catalyst for Payment Reform, two independent health policy groups.', '43 States Flunk When it Comes to Healthcare Price Transparency, Groups Say', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '43-states-flunk-when-it-comes-to-healthcare-price-transparency-groups-say', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:49:13', '2017-10-05 08:49:13', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=247', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(248, 1, '2017-10-05 08:49:33', '2017-10-05 08:49:33', 'California''s public hospitals will receive up to $472 million annually for the remaining four years of a waiver meant to reform the state''s Medicaid program.', 'California Will Get Nearly $2 Billion in Uncompensated-Care Funds', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'california-will-get-nearly-2-billion-in-uncompensated-care-funds', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:49:33', '2017-10-05 08:49:33', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=248', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(249, 1, '2017-10-05 08:49:49', '2017-10-05 08:49:49', 'Despite receiving huge subsidies, insurers suffered larger losses selling qualified health plans in the individual market than they did selling nearly identical policies in the small group market, a new study from George Mason University has found.', 'Insurers Suffer Large Losses in Individual Market, George Mason University Report Finds', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'insurers-suffer-large-losses-in-individual-market-george-mason-university-report-finds', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:49:49', '2017-10-05 08:49:49', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=249', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(250, 1, '2017-10-05 08:50:10', '2017-10-05 08:50:10', 'ACA calls for reductions in DSH payments, and other federal policy changes are focused on limiting the use of supplemental payments, analysis shows.', 'Affordable Care Act Policy Changes Could Severely Impact Hospital Financial Viability', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'affordable-care-act-policy-changes-could-severely-impact-hospital-financial-viability', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:50:10', '2017-10-05 08:50:10', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=250', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2017-10-05 08:50:26', '2017-10-05 08:50:26', 'The American College of Emergency Physicians is suing the Department of Health and Human Services and other federal agencies for setting payment rules that result in inadequate reimbursement for out-of-network emergency medical services, according to the civil lawsuit filed in U.S. District Court on May 12.', 'American College of Emergency Physicians Sues HHS Over Emergency Payment Rules', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'american-college-of-emergency-physicians-sues-hhs-over-emergency-payment-rules', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:50:26', '2017-10-05 08:50:26', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=251', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(252, 1, '2017-10-05 08:50:43', '2017-10-05 08:50:43', 'Bipartisan legislation introduced Wednesday by the leaders of the House Ways and Means Subcommittee on Health resolves two provisions of the Bipartisan Budget Act of 2015 in allowing hospitals that are building outpatient facilities off-campus to be paid at higher reimbursement rates, and in taking into consideration for payment, socioeconomic status.', 'Legislation Would Allow for Higher Outpatient, Off-Campus Payment Rates', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'legislation-would-allow-for-higher-outpatient-off-campus-payment-rates', '', '', '2017-10-05 08:50:43', '2017-10-05 08:50:43', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=252', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(253, 1, '2017-10-05 08:50:59', '2017-10-05 08:50:59', 'Pamela Peele knows that people who subscribe to cooking magazines have a much higher risk of going to the emergency room. But how she knows that is a whole other story.', 'Analyze This: Health Systems, Health Plans Get to the Core of Big Data', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'analyze-this-health-systems-health-plans-get-to-the-core-of-big-data', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:50:08', '2017-10-05 09:50:08', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=253', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(254, 1, '2017-10-05 08:51:15', '2017-10-05 08:51:15', 'A bill that would give Florida residents greater transparency on healthcare costs is headed to Gov. Rick Scott. The Florida Senate passed the bill (HB 1175) by a 34-1 vote Friday, which was the final day of the legislative session.', 'Florida Bill on Healthcare Transparency Headed to Governor', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'florida-bill-on-healthcare-transparency-headed-to-governor', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:50:27', '2017-10-05 09:50:27', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=254', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(255, 1, '2017-10-05 08:51:35', '2017-10-05 08:51:35', 'A type of pain that hospitals thought they had relieved has come back with a vengeance: it‚Äôs called bad debt. Hospitals have long struggled to collect bills when patients aren‚Äôt covered by insurance -- creating delinquent accounts. The Affordable Care Act was supposed to relieve some of that strain by helping pay for coverage for millions of Americans and expanding Medicaid in some states to cover the poor.', 'Bad Debt Is the Pain Hospitals Can''t Heal as Patients Don''t Pay', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bad-debt-is-the-pain-hospitals-cant-heal-as-patients-dont-pay', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:50:46', '2017-10-05 09:50:46', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=255', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2017-10-05 08:51:52', '2017-10-05 08:51:52', 'The four major health insurers currently pushing for mergers ‚Äî Aetna and Humana, and Anthem and Cigna ‚Äî are still a long way from gaining federal approval. But they say they''re optimistic their respective deals will close by year-end, in part because they have had success getting the nod from state regulators.', 'Insurance Deals Win Over States, but Feds Still in Doubt', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'insurance-deals-win-over-states-but-feds-still-in-doubt', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:49:51', '2017-10-05 09:49:51', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=256', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(257, 1, '2017-10-05 08:52:13', '2017-10-05 08:52:13', 'About 12.7 million Americans signed up for 2016 health insurance coverage through the government insurance exchanges, surpassing its expectations, U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Sylvia Burwell said on Thursday.', 'Nearly 13 Million Sign Up for Obamacare Health Insurance', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nearly-13-million-sign-up-for-obamacare-health-insurance', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:49:28', '2017-10-05 09:49:28', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=257', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(258, 1, '2017-10-05 08:52:30', '2017-10-05 08:52:30', 'It''s not about cost, but value, according to a panel of revenue cycle professionals who work in health systems that often charge more for care than other providers.', 'Healthcare Providers Must Weigh High Value vs. High Prices', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthcare-providers-must-weigh-high-value-vs-high-prices', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:49:17', '2017-10-05 09:49:17', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=258', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(259, 1, '2017-10-05 08:52:47', '2017-10-05 08:52:47', 'The boundary between being a provider and a payer is blurring as hospitals face more risk, according to Joe Nichols of Health Data Consulting, prompting health systems to make changes to keep from losing too much money.', 'More Risk Shifting to Hospitals, Pressuring Revenue Cycle, Experts Say', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'more-risk-shifting-to-hospitals-pressuring-revenue-cycle-experts-say', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:49:12', '2017-10-05 09:49:12', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=259', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(260, 1, '2017-10-05 08:53:04', '2017-10-05 08:53:04', 'New health insurance data from the U.S. Census Bureau shows the uninsured rate has dropped in all 50 states and the District of Columbia.¬†The numbers, which include data from calendar year 2013 and calendar year 2014, show the states that chose to expand Medicaid and/or run their own health insurance marketplace saw the greatest decrease in the number of uninsured.', '20 States with the Largest Drop in Uninsured Rates', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-states-with-the-largest-drop-in-uninsured-rates', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:47:42', '2017-10-05 09:47:42', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=260', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(261, 1, '2017-10-05 08:53:19', '2017-10-05 08:53:19', 'For providers to thrive under healthcare payment and delivery model reform, the patient experience must align with the patient expectation.', 'The Culture of Patient Experience', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-culture-of-patient-experience', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:48:04', '2017-10-05 09:48:04', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=261', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(262, 1, '2017-10-05 08:53:41', '2017-10-05 08:53:41', 'In 2012, the U.S. Supreme Court gave states the option to expand Medicaid under Obamacare and Florida has chosen not to expand. There are principled reasons for declining to grow a program that currently covers 3.7 million Floridians at a cost of $23.5 billion per year, or about one-third of Florida''s budget.', 'Crisafulli: Why the Florida House Opposes Medicaid Expansion', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'crisafulli-why-the-florida-house-opposes-medicaid-expansion', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:48:23', '2017-10-05 09:48:23', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=262', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(263, 1, '2017-10-05 08:53:58', '2017-10-05 08:53:58', 'In a word, it is all about interoperability. Appearing together for a keynote session at HIMSS15, ONC chief Karen DeSalvo, M.D., and CMS Acting Administrator Andy Slavitt made it clear that vendors, providers and the government need to pick up the pace on an issue that has vexed the industry for the past decade or more.', 'CMS Chief Says Interoperability is the ‚ÄòPrice to Play‚Äô', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-chief-says-interoperability-is-the-price-to-play', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:48:35', '2017-10-05 09:48:35', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=263', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(264, 1, '2017-10-05 08:54:16', '2017-10-05 08:54:16', 'Texas officials and the Obama administration are nearing a showdown over Medicaid expansion that threatens billions of dollars of federal funding that helps healthcare providers care for low-income Texans and improve the quality of care.', 'CMS Takes Tougher Medicaid Stance to Texas', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-takes-tougher-medicaid-stance-to-texas', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:48:49', '2017-10-05 09:48:49', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=264', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(265, 1, '2017-10-05 08:54:31', '2017-10-05 08:54:31', 'Sixteen months after going live, the insurance company Oscar has joined the elite group of start-ups known as unicorns, or those with billion-dollar valuations.', 'Oscar, a Health Insurance Start-Up, Valued at $1.5 Billion', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'oscar-a-health-insurance-start-up-valued-at-1-5-billion', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:46:47', '2017-10-05 09:46:47', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=265', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(266, 1, '2017-10-05 08:54:47', '2017-10-05 08:54:47', 'The uninsured rate among U.S. adults declined to 11.9% for the first quarter of 2015 -- down one percentage point from the previous quarter and 5.2 points since the end of 2013, just before the Affordable Care Act went into effect. The uninsured rate is the lowest since Gallup and Healthways began tracking it in 2008.', 'In U.S., Uninsured Rate Dips to 11.9% in First Quarter', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'in-u-s-uninsured-rate-dips-to-11-9-in-first-quarter', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:46:55', '2017-10-05 09:46:55', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=266', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(267, 1, '2017-10-05 08:55:06', '2017-10-05 08:55:06', 'As the economy improves and employees spend more on health care, employer-paid premiums are rising again with an increase of 5.5 percent forecast for 2015 with worker premiums and out-of-pocket costs ‚Äì which have doubled since 2009 ‚Äì rising at an even faster clip.', 'Worker Out-Of-Pocket Health Costs Have Doubled In Five Years', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'worker-out-of-pocket-health-costs-have-doubled-in-five-years', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:47:03', '2017-10-05 09:47:03', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=267', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(268, 1, '2017-10-05 08:55:24', '2017-10-05 08:55:24', 'Today‚Äôs report shows that while enrollment in states that expanded Medicaid has risen by 22 percent since before open enrollment in the Marketplace began, states that have not expanded reported only a 5 percent increase in enrollment during this same period.', 'Medicaid and CHIP Enrollment Grows by 8.7 Million Additional Americans', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'medicaid-and-chip-enrollment-grows-by-8-7-million-additional-americans', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:47:22', '2017-10-05 09:47:22', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=268', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(269, 1, '2017-10-05 08:55:41', '2017-10-05 08:55:41', 'Chris Van Gorder, CEO of Scripps Health, has been a remarkable leader for the San Diego-based, five-hospital system. After joining the system in 2000, at a time when the medical staff had voted no confidence in the previous administration and the system was losing millions, Chris led its remarkable $150 million turnaround. And he did so without any layoffs. Today, Scripps'' facilities routinely appear in national hospital rankings, and the system recently opened a $220 million cancer center and has a $450 million cardiac center in the works.', 'Email 10 Leadership Lessons From "The Front-Line Leader"', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'email-10-leadership-lessons-from-the-front-line-leader', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:45:59', '2017-10-05 09:45:59', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=269', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(270, 1, '2017-10-05 08:55:55', '2017-10-05 08:55:55', 'After a year fully in place, the Affordable Care Act has largely succeeded in delivering on President Obama‚Äôs main promises, an analysis by a team of reporters and data researchers shows. But it has also fallen short in some ways and given rise to a powerful conservative backlash.', 'Is the Affordable Care Act Working?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'is-the-affordable-care-act-working', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:46:08', '2017-10-05 09:46:08', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=270', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(271, 1, '2017-10-05 08:56:15', '2017-10-05 08:56:15', 'As we approach the one-year anniversary of Obamacare‚Äôs launch, the pundits continue to argue over whether or not it‚Äôs working. Meanwhile, something much bigger is happening. Whatever you think of its merits, the Affordable Care Act is re-shaping American healthcare, radically altering business models that hadn‚Äôt changed in decades.', 'Like It Or Not, Obamacare Is Reshaping The Healthcare Industry', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'like-it-or-not-obamacare-is-reshaping-the-healthcare-industry', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:46:25', '2017-10-05 09:46:25', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=271', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(272, 1, '2017-10-05 08:56:29', '2017-10-05 08:56:29', 'Melody Rempe spends much of her day telling people who are about to go into the hospital how much they‚Äôll have to pay. As a patient financial counselor at Nebraska Methodist Health System, she calls patients about a week before they go in for procedures with estimates of their bills and what portion insurance will cover.', 'Why Hospitals Want Patients to Pay Upfront', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'why-hospitals-want-patients-to-pay-upfront', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:45:23', '2017-10-05 09:45:23', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=272', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(273, 1, '2017-10-05 08:56:44', '2017-10-05 08:56:44', 'The Obama administration has a new projection (PDF) of the benefit hospitals will enjoy this year as they provide less care that no one pays for: $5.7 billion. Hospitals in states that expanded Medicaid are getting most of it.', 'Hospitals'' Uncompensated Care Will Drop $5.7 Billion This Year: HHS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospitals-uncompensated-care-will-drop-5-7-billion-this-year-hhs', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:45:35', '2017-10-05 09:45:35', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=273', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(274, 1, '2017-10-05 08:57:02', '2017-10-05 08:57:02', 'In 1000 BC, the only early test for diabetes was whether your urine attracted ants. In 2012, 25.8 million United States residents with diabetes spent USD 245 billion on diabetes, a figure presently rising by 7% per annum.', 'How Technology Is Going To Disrupt Health Care', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-technology-is-going-to-disrupt-health-care', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:44:05', '2017-10-05 09:44:05', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=274', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(275, 1, '2017-10-05 08:57:17', '2017-10-05 08:57:17', 'In advance of ICD-10 implementation scheduled for Oct. 1 of next year, the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) plans to conduct end-to-end testing in January to identify issues in the system that need to be addressed. Physicians who are interested in participating should apply by Oct. 3.', 'CMS Conducting End-to-End ICD-10 Testing; Apply by Oct. 3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-conducting-end-to-end-icd-10-testing-apply-by-oct-3', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:43:59', '2017-10-05 09:43:59', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=275', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2017-10-05 08:57:31', '2017-10-05 08:57:31', 'If there''s any application of IT in healthcare that can resonate with CFOs, it''s revenue cycle. On average, hospitals in the U.S. write off between 3 and 17 percent of their revenue due to payer denials.', 'Leverage Revenue Cycle Systems To Stop Hemorrhaging Money', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leverage-revenue-cycle-systems-to-stop-hemorrhaging-money', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:43:41', '2017-10-05 09:43:41', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=276', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(277, 1, '2017-10-05 08:57:46', '2017-10-05 08:57:46', 'Payment reform in health care is confusing, but the goal is simple: How can health care providers change their economic incentives to encourage value over volume? If you''ve wondered about how these new payment models work, we''re here to help.', 'The Beginner''s Guide to New Health Care Payment Models', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-beginners-guide-to-new-health-care-payment-models', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:43:26', '2017-10-05 09:43:26', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=277', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(278, 1, '2017-10-05 08:58:06', '2017-10-05 08:58:06', 'Hospital bills may soon get a lot simpler. Traditionally, hospitals have charged patients separately for every service and supply they use‚Äîas anybody who has waded through pages of charges knows. Fees for surgeons, anesthesiologists and other providers come in complex bills of their own.', 'Hospitals Push Bundled Care as the Billing Plan of the Future', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hospitals-push-bundled-care-as-the-billing-plan-of-the-future', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:43:04', '2017-10-05 09:43:04', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=278', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
(279, 1, '2017-10-05 08:58:36', '2017-10-05 08:58:36', 'Many hospitals face further decreased Medicare reimbursements next year, as CMS released its proposed rule for the fiscal year 2015 Medicare inpatient prospective payment system.', 'CMS'' 2015 IPPS Proposed Rule: 10 Points to Know', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cms-2015-ipps-proposed-rule-10-points-to-know', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:42:50', '2017-10-05 09:42:50', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=industry_news&#038;p=279', 0, 'industry_news', '', 0),
