(282, 1, '2017-10-05 09:43:00', '2017-10-05 09:43:00', 'Hospital bills may soon get a lot simpler. Traditionally, hospitals have charged patients separately for every service and supply they use‚Äîas anybody who has waded through pages of charges knows. Fees for surgeons, anesthesiologists and other providers come in complex bills of their own.', 'Hospitals Push Bundled Care as the Billing Plan of the Future', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '278-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:43:00', '2017-10-05 09:43:00', '', 278, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//278-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(283, 1, '2017-10-05 09:55:46', '2017-10-05 09:55:46', 'Ascension''s advertising has taken a decidedly digital turn as the Catholic giant rebrands all of its facilities. St. Louis-based Ascension joins many other health systems that are moving more of their marketing budgets to digital and away from traditional media because that''s where consumers are going first to research their conditions and providers, marketing executives say.', 'Hospitals Work to Harness the Power of Digital Marketing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '197-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 09:55:46', '2017-10-05 09:55:46', '', 197, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//197-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(284, 1, '2017-10-05 10:04:39', '2017-10-05 10:04:39', 'The Ensemble Patient Access and Patient Accounts teams at Portneuf Medical Center in Idaho recently collected donations for a school supply drive to benefit Jefferson Elementary School. The team was proud to support Jefferson Elementary''s goal of preparing students for the future by educating the whole child; intellectually, socially, emotionally, and physically.', 'Ensemble''s Portneuf Medical Center Associates Donate School Supplies to Jefferson Elementary', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensembles-portneuf-medical-center-associates-donate-school-supplies-to-jefferson-elementary', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:04:39', '2017-10-05 10:04:39', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=284', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(285, 1, '2017-10-05 10:04:51', '2017-10-05 10:04:51', 'Hurricane Harvey and the flooding that came after has created one of the largest disasters in the U.S. The storm inflicted widespread devastation on the area, and federal officials have already indicated it will take years to rebuild from the destruction. Ensemble Health Partners associates across the country have shown their support of the Harvey Relief efforts, both monetarily to the American Red Cross (with a matching contribution from Ensemble Health Partners), as well as in support of a supply drive to help with the rebuild.', 'Hurricane Harvey Relief', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hurricane-harvey-relief', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:04:51', '2017-10-05 10:04:51', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=285', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(286, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:00', '2017-10-05 10:05:00', 'Ensemble associates at Hackensack Meridian Health Pascack Valley Medical Center volunteered today at the Community Food Bank of New Jersey. The mission of the Community Food Bank is to fight hunger and poverty in New Jersey by assisting those in need and seeking long-term solutions. Last year, the Community Food Bank distributed over 50 million pounds of food through more than 1,000 community partners like local soup kitchens and food pantries. This food ‚Äì all 42 million meals ‚Äì reached people in need across the state. We are proud of our associates in New Jersey that participated in this Ensemble Gives Back activity.', 'Ensemble''s Pascack Valley Team Gives Back', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensembles-pascack-valley-team-gives-back', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:00', '2017-10-05 10:05:00', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=286', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(287, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:11', '2017-10-05 10:05:11', 'Today, Ensemble hosted a Night at the Ballpark in partnership with the Charlotte Knights. All proceeds from the event were donated to Beds for Kids, an organization that helps families that do not have furniture for their home, benefiting children and their families in the Charlotte area.', 'Ensemble Teams Up With the Charlotte Knights to Support Beds for Kids', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-teams-up-with-the-charlotte-knights-to-support-beds-for-kids', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:11', '2017-10-05 10:05:11', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=287', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(288, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:20', '2017-10-05 10:05:20', 'Ensemble partnered with Habitat for Humanity on a home building project to help a deserving family in the Charlotte area move into a home they might not have been able to afford otherwise. Volunteers from Ensemble installed a ‚ÄúHugs‚Äù safety rail system along the perimeter of the roof.', 'Ensemble Partners With Habitat for Humanity to Help a Family in Need', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-partners-with-habitat-for-humanity-to-help-a-family-in-need', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:20', '2017-10-05 10:05:20', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=288', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(289, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:28', '2017-10-05 10:05:28', 'Ensemble has partnered with HFMA to bring HFMA''s national Women''s Leadership Conference ‚Äì HERe ‚Äì to Ensemble. The HERe initiative is an effort that aims to inspire not only women but men invested in the professional development of women leaders in the health care field with the tools and resources they need to succeed.\r\n\r\nThroughout this event, conference attendees learned about career development, skill building and the unique challenges facing women healthcare leaders in balancing their personal and professional lives. This is a pilot program made possible through Ensemble‚Äôs partnership with HFMA ‚Äì and the first time that HFMA has offering this career development program directly to employers.', 'Ensemble Partners With HFMA on National Women''s Leadership Conference - HERe', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-partners-with-hfma-on-national-womens-leadership-conference-here', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:28', '2017-10-05 10:05:28', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=289', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(290, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:38', '2017-10-05 10:05:38', 'Ensemble Health Partners associates raised over $15,000 to support the American Cancer Society Relay for Life event in Huntersville, NC. The money raised through Relay for Life events helps realize the American Cancer Society‚Äôs mission to save lives, celebrate life and lead the fight for a world without cancer. Donations are used to fund life-saving cancer research, patient support services, prevention and education information and detection and treatment programs.', 'Ensemble Health Partners Associates Donate $15,000 to Support Relay for Life', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-health-partners-associates-donate-15000-to-support-relay-for-life', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:38', '2017-10-05 10:05:38', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=290', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(291, 1, '2017-10-05 10:05:53', '2017-10-05 10:05:53', 'We are pleased to welcome three new leaders to the Ensemble Patient Access team at HackensackUMC Mountainside in New Jersey:\r\n\r\n‚Ä¢ Lesly Vece, Director, Patient Access\r\n‚Ä¢ Renee Howson, Manager, Patient Access\r\n‚Ä¢ Maria Martinez, Manager, Patient Access\r\n\r\nLesly previously served as Director of Patient Access at Saint Clare‚Äôs Health System, where she oversaw all functions of Patient Access at four Saint Clare‚Äôs hospitals. In this role, she had oversight of 68 team members and over 55 services at the hospital.\r\n\r\nRenee joins the team from Good Samaritan Hospital, where she previously held a similar role as Patient Access Manager. In this role, she was responsible for overseeing the daily operation of the Patient Access department with a staff of 30 registrars and two supervisors.\r\n\r\nMaria joins us from Saint Clare‚Äôs Health System, where she was the Manager of Central Scheduling and Financial Counseling. She brings a strong background in customer relations and her dedication to serving patients, team members and clients will be a great addition to the team.', 'Welcome New Patient Access Leaders', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'welcome-new-patient-access-leaders', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:05:53', '2017-10-05 10:05:53', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=291', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(292, 1, '2017-10-05 10:06:11', '2017-10-05 10:06:11', 'We are pleased to announce the promotion of Mike Bartlett to Senior Director, Revenue Cycle. In this role, Mike oversees all AR services across all Ensemble clients.', 'Mike Bartlett Named Senior Director, Revenue Cycle', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mike-bartlett-named-senior-director-revenue-cycle', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:06:11', '2017-10-05 10:06:11', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=292', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(293, 1, '2017-10-05 10:06:22', '2017-10-05 10:06:22', 'Ensemble Health Partners is pleased to welcome Shannon White as Senior Vice President, Revenue Cycle. Shannon is a senior revenue cycle operations executive with a proven history of leading successful teams to implement financial systems and strategies that improve financial performance.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Ensemble, Shannon served as vice president of the Shared Services Center for Fort Smith, LLC, a subsidiary of Community Health Systems. She oversaw the growth of the Shared Service Center from a standalone business office to 53 facilities operating in nine states.\r\n\r\nWorking with the governor of Arkansas, she negotiated $22 million in rebate programs and economic development incentives for the organization. Under her leadership, her team grew to more than 700 team members. Within Fort Smith, this growth was a tremendous accomplishment and reflective of her organization becoming the employer of choice. Through various cost savings initiatives and efficiency, she improved cost to collect, year over year. She also maintained a cash collection to net revenue percentage of 103% or above annually and led a reduction of net AR days to 53.', 'Ensemble Welcomes Shannon White, Senior Vice President, Revenue Cycle', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-welcomes-shannon-white-senior-vice-president-revenue-cycle', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:06:22', '2017-10-05 10:06:22', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=293', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(294, 1, '2017-10-05 10:06:34', '2017-10-05 10:06:34', 'Ensemble Health Partners is pleased to announced that it was recently honored by the Lake Norman Chamber of Commerce for its efforts in diversity at the Lake Norman Chamber Diversity luncheon. The chamber selected Ensemble Health Partners as one of its Corporate Champions of Diversity finalists.', 'Ensemble Health Partners Named Corporate Champions of Diversity Finalists by Lake Norman Chamber of Commerce', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-health-partners-named-corporate-champions-of-diversity-finalists-by-lake-norman-chamber-of-commerce', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:35:07', '2017-10-05 10:35:07', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=294', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(295, 1, '2017-10-05 10:07:54', '2017-10-05 10:07:54', 'Ensemble Health Partners, headquartered in Huntersville, is expanding into 30,000 square feet, at 13620 Reese Blvd East, Suite 200 in The Park Huntersville, to accommodate their rapid growth. The company plans to create 120 jobs immediately with continued growth in the coming years. The 120 employees hired will begin work this summer.', 'Ensemble Health Partners Growing in Huntersville', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-health-partners-growing-in-huntersville', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:34:46', '2017-10-05 10:34:46', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=295', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(296, 1, '2017-10-05 10:08:11', '2017-10-05 10:08:11', 'Huntersville‚Äôs new 674-acre development off Gilead Road is about to get its biggest tenant to date. Ensemble Health Partners is about to move into a 30,870-square-foot space in the park‚Äôs Alexander Building next month and will be hiring an additional 120 full time employees in the process.', 'Ensemble Health Partners Expanding', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-health-partners-expanding', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:34:36', '2017-10-05 10:34:36', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=296', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(297, 1, '2017-10-05 10:08:52', '2017-10-05 10:08:52', 'Ensemble Health Partners is pleased to announce that Pieter Schouten has joined as Chief Analytics Officer. Schouten has extensive experience in creating advanced analytics and cognitive computing solutions for firms in the healthcare industry and for Fortune 500 companies.', 'Ensemble Health Partners Welcomes Advanced Analytics Expert Pieter Schouten', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ensemble-health-partners-welcomes-advanced-analytics-expert-pieter-schouten', '', '', '2017-10-05 10:09:11', '2017-10-05 10:09:11', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=press&#038;p=297', 0, 'press', '', 0),
