(326, 1, '2017-10-07 06:43:09', '2017-10-07 06:43:09', '<p>Our website has a lot to say about experience. We also understand that there is a lot to be said for gaining this experience. If learning the Healthcare Revenue Cycle by working alongside some of industries leading minds and getting a hands on training approach is something that interests you, we have a lot more we would like to talk to you about.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As an Associate, you can expect to work with a team of operational leaders who are focused not only on the needs of the client, but also on ensuring you have the opportunities and support needed to reach your professional development objectives. You will report to an experienced Manager, but will also work shoulder to shoulder with Directors, Vice Presidents and the Managing Partners as well. You will have the opportunity to gain experience in each segment of the revenue cycle process including: Patient Access, Health Information Management, Accounts Receivable Management, Denials and Appeals, and Client Relations. You are expected to meet project timelines and produce deliverables, while managing a busy training program and balancing operational and client needs, but you will also be provided a first person view of why this industry is so rewarding and what fuels our passion for excellence. Self-study and development are key requirements for an associate to gain additional knowledge and experiences for their development.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Associates are expected to demonstrate refined technical and communication skills, as well as the ability to work effectively in both independent and group settings, in order to develop effective solutions. Position responsibilities allow you to work hands-on work within multiple revenue cycle functions, data gathering, organizing ideas into actionable tasks, structuring documents and electronic data, financial modeling, performing both qualitative and quantitative analyses, identifying trends, and compiling and implementing effective solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>If limitless potential in career growth excites you and the following descriptions sound like you profile, click apply. We can''t wait to get to know you.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Undergraduate Bachelor''s degree majoring related to Health Care, Accounting, Finance, Engineering, Computer Science, and/or Consulting required.</li>\r\n                                <li>Cumulative GPA of 3.0 or above</li>\r\n                                <li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Exceptional verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Strong computer skills including Microsoft Office, specifically Excel, Access, PowerPoint, and Word</li>\r\n                                <li>Willingness to participate in self-study and continued education to learn the changing healthcare industry</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Cycle Associate', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-cycle-associate', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:43:09', '2017-10-07 06:43:09', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=326', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(327, 1, '2017-10-07 06:43:56', '2017-10-07 06:43:56', '<p>Our website has a lot to say about experience. We also understand that there is a lot to be said for gaining this experience. If learning the Healthcare Revenue Cycle by working alongside some of industries leading minds and getting a hands on training approach is something that interests you, we have a lot more we would like to talk to you about.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As an Associate, you can expect to work with a team of operational leaders who are focused not only on the needs of the client, but also on ensuring you have the opportunities and support needed to reach your professional development objectives. You will report to an experienced Manager, but will also work shoulder to shoulder with Directors, Vice Presidents and the Managing Partners as well. You will have the opportunity to gain experience in each segment of the revenue cycle process including: Patient Access, Health Information Management, Accounts Receivable Management, Denials and Appeals, and Client Relations. You are expected to meet project timelines and produce deliverables, while managing a busy training program and balancing operational and client needs, but you will also be provided a first person view of why this industry is so rewarding and what fuels our passion for excellence. Self-study and development are key requirements for an associate to gain additional knowledge and experiences for their development.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Associates are expected to demonstrate refined technical and communication skills, as well as the ability to work effectively in both independent and group settings, in order to develop effective solutions. Position responsibilities allow you to work hands-on work within multiple revenue cycle functions, data gathering, organizing ideas into actionable tasks, structuring documents and electronic data, financial modeling, performing both qualitative and quantitative analyses, identifying trends, and compiling and implementing effective solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>If limitless potential in career growth excites you and the following descriptions sound like you profile, click apply. We can''t wait to get to know you.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Undergraduate Bachelor''s degree majoring related to Health Care, Accounting, Finance, Engineering, Computer Science, and/or Consulting required.</li>\r\n                                <li>Cumulative GPA of 3.0 or above</li>\r\n                                <li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Exceptional verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Strong computer skills including Microsoft Office, specifically Excel, Access, PowerPoint, and Word</li>\r\n                                <li>Willingness to participate in self-study and continued education to learn the changing healthcare industry</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Cycle Associate 2', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-cycle-associate-2__trashed', '', '', '2017-10-07 07:06:57', '2017-10-07 07:06:57', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=327', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(328, 1, '2017-10-07 06:50:20', '2017-10-07 06:50:20', ' <p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Revenue Recovery Specialist will support, and report to the Manager of Revenue Recovery. The Specialist will be responsible for researching and analyzing accounts for assigned clients and payers to diagnose reasons for under payment or non-payment of claims. Duties include ascertaining trends that emerge during review and developing strategies to correct and collect on accounts. The Revenue Recovery Specialist will also develop strong working relationships with the assigned client and team members.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place team members in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths. We will be looking for candidates with background in Insurance follow-up, insurance collections and reviewing patient accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates who feel that they fit the following would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>3-5 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance, Hospital specific</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor''s degree in Finance, Business, Accounting or a Healthcare specific field required</li>\r\n                                <li>Keen understanding of the Revenue Cycle and the opportunity for uncollected revenue</li>\r\n                                <li>Working knowledge of CPT/HCPCS codes</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal and Written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to Analyze and identify trends</li>\r\n                                <li>Aptitude for and the ability to adapt to multiple software systems presented by clients</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>Comfortable with being on the phone with various parties for the greatest part of the day &ndash; capable of creating a professional and competent presence over the phone</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Recovery Specialist', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-recovery-specialist', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:50:20', '2017-10-07 06:50:20', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=328', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(329, 1, '2017-10-07 06:50:49', '2017-10-07 06:50:49', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for leaders with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Revenue Recovery Manager will support the Director of Revenue Recovery in the selection, direction and development of department team members, and will report to the Director of Revenue Recovery. The Manager will be responsible for assisting Team members with problematic claims and questions regarding processes. Position duties include managing the daily work-flow of the department, monitoring progress to identify trending issues and develop training or processes to address these issues. The Manager will also hold huddles to efficiently cover new or evolving training focuses to encourage and develop team members. The Manager will be responsible for overseeing progress on the floor and monitoring the worked accounts for quality assurance.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Leadership within Ensemble work for our team members and our clients. While there is a lot of responsibility within the leadership role, there is also an opportunity to influence, guide and encourage the team members you work for. As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place leaders in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates that exemplify the following traits would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>3-5 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance Claims and working knowledge of healthcare Revenue Cycle required, hospital specific insurance experience preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>2-4 years of previous supervisory experience, preferably within the healthcare setting, required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent working knowledge of the Hospital revenue cycle and of revenue recovery required.</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor''s degree in Finance, Business, Accounting or a Healthcare specific field required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal skills and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Proven Leadership skills &ndash; the ability to motivate and lead in a team-based productivity environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Resourcefulness, Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>A Player that has insight into associates and accounts, shows exceptional intelligence and has the ability to motivate teams</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Recovery Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-recovery-manager', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:50:49', '2017-10-07 06:50:49', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=329', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(330, 1, '2017-10-07 06:51:19', '2017-10-07 06:51:19', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Revenue Cycle Manager will support the Director of Revenue Cycle in the selection, direction and development of department team members, and will report to the Director of Revenue Cycle. The Manager will be responsible for assisting Team members with problematic claims and questions regarding processes. Position duties include managing the daily work-flow of the department, monitoring progress to identify trending issues and develop training or processes to address these issues. The Manager will also hold huddles to efficiently cover new or evolving training focuses to encourage and develop team members. The Manager will be responsible for overseeing progress on the floor and monitoring the worked accounts for quality assurance.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Leadership within Ensemble work for our team members and our clients. While there is a lot of responsibility within the leadership role, there is also an opportunity to influence, guide and encourage the team members you work for. As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place leaders in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates that exemplify the following traits would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>3-5 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance Claims and working knowledge of healthcare Revenue Cycle required, hospital specific insurance experience preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>2-4 years of previous supervisory experience, preferably within the healthcare setting, required</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor''s degree in Finance, Business, Accounting or a Healthcare specific field required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal skills and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Proven Leadership skills &ndash; the ability to motivate and lead in a team-based productivity environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Resourcefulness, Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>A Player that has insight into associates and accounts, shows exceptional intelligence and has the ability to motivate teams</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Cycle Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-cycle-manager', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:51:19', '2017-10-07 06:51:19', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=330', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(331, 1, '2017-10-07 06:51:55', '2017-10-07 06:51:55', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is always looking to partner with Revenue Cycle Consultants who have robust experience within Healthcare Revenue Cycle and an eye for process improvement. The Consultant position is a great example of our appreciation for diversity, passion for career growth, and client centric mindset as the focus for this position is entirely based around client needs and the particular expertise of the consultant. If you have a career history of valuable contributions within the realm of patient access, HIM/coding, charge capture, revenue integrity, billing, collections or any other area of the revenue cycle, we would love to discuss our opportunities with you.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Revenue Cycle Consultant', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'revenue-cycle-consultant', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:51:55', '2017-10-07 06:51:55', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=331', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(332, 1, '2017-10-07 06:52:25', '2017-10-07 06:52:25', ' <p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Regional Patient Access Director will travel frequently for 3+ sites in multi-state client locations with PADs reporting to them.  The Regional Patient Access Director oversees the Patient Access Directors. The Director assists in the training of onsite leadership, providing direction on process improvement and overseeing the implementation of root cause solutions. Other responsibilities include reporting on the progress of department developments, representing the registration function during leadership updates, identifying inefficiencies and developing solutions to the address the obstacles discovered and reviewing the work performed at the hospital level.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p><strong>Experience: 3-5 years‚Äô experience in healthcare insurance and hospital revenue cycle required. 5-7 years of previous management or supervisory experience, preferably in a healthcare environment, required. Excellent working knowledge of the hospital revenue cycle required.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n                            <p><b>Position Requires:</b></p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills. </li>\r\n                                <li>Problem-solving and strong observation skills needed to observe processes and performance, then generate useful information from it. </li>\r\n                                <li>Leadership skills, as well as, the ability to motivate and lead in a team-based productivity environment. </li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to changing procedures and growing environment. </li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty. </li>\r\n                                <li>An internal drive to succeed and pride in personal accomplishments. </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p><b>Licenses/Certificates:</b> Must pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association of hire, unless already certified.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Regional Patient Access Director', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'regional-patient-access-director', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:52:25', '2017-10-07 06:52:25', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=332', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(333, 1, '2017-10-07 06:52:52', '2017-10-07 06:52:52', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Payment Posting Specialist is mainly responsible for timely and accurate reporting of cash receivables to the billing system. Cash posting or Payment posting is sometimes known as payment application, as the specialist manages the application of payments made on accounts whether received from group health payers, patient or private pay methods, or Worker&#39;s compensation insurance. Posting is done on a daily basis, to ensure records accurately reflect receipt of payment on charges. The associate may also generate and review cash application reports.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place team members in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths. We will be looking for candidates with background in general accounting or payment processing, with firm understanding of debits and credits.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates who feel that they fit the following would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>1-3 years experience working with cash or payment application with a working knowledge of accounting fundamentals. Hospital specific insurance experience is beneficial but not required.</li>\r\n                                <li>Associates degree preferred, High school Diploma or equivalent required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent accuracy and attention to detail</li>\r\n                                <li>Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Payment Posting/Cash Application Specialist', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'payment-postingcash-application-specialist', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:52:52', '2017-10-07 06:52:52', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=333', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(334, 1, '2017-10-07 06:54:13', '2017-10-07 06:54:13', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking for a Nurse Auditor who has a comprehensive understanding of medical terminology, hospital inpatient and/or outpatient coding, charge capture, CDM, case management experience and medical records. The candidate must be organized, detail-oriented, accurate, and professional and would, ideally, possess CPC certification and other coding credentials/clinical expertise.  The ideal candidate for this position can approach problem-solving challenges independently, has strong attention to detail and enjoys working in a fast-paced, collaborative and team-based environment.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p><b>Essential Functions:</b></p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Achieve and maintain assigned client financial performance goals </li>\r\n                                <li>Validation of potential missing charges, coding variances, and overcharges using proprietary technology and medical records </li>\r\n                                <li>Assist in prediction enhancements to increase verification rates </li>\r\n                                <li>Establish proficiency working in Opera, reviewing reports about revenue leakage and missing charges </li>\r\n                                <li>Responsible for CDM, Charge Capture, Charge Reconciliation, and failed claim edit resolution.  Will also play a role in managing Discharged Not Final Charge (DNFB) </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p><b>Qualifications:</b></p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Must have a Bachelor‚Äôs of Science Degree </li>\r\n                                <li>RN/BSN required, coding certification is a plus </li>\r\n                                <li>3+ years of hospital auditing/coding experience with CPT, ICD, HCPCS and modifier coding </li>\r\n                                <li>Experience working within the hospital environment preferred </li>\r\n                                <li>Nurse Auditor Experience </li>\r\n                                <li>Self-sufficient with strong analytical and research skills </li>\r\n                                <li>Working knowledge of hospital charging practices, payer reimbursement methodology, medical necessity criteria, and applicable industry based standards </li>\r\n                                <li>Remain current on CPT, ICD, HCPC and modifier coding requirements  </li>\r\n                                <li>Experience preferred with one or more of the following specialties: Interventional Radiology, Invasive 	<li>Cardiology, General Surgery, Orthopedic Surgery, Vascular Surgery, and Surgical Oncology </li>\r\n                                <li>Proficient using Microsoft Office products and the ability to work effectively with computerized programs and databases </li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to communicate effectively  </li>\r\n                                <li>Demonstrate independent judgment, discretion, and decision making abilities </li>\r\n                                <li>Self-motivated, hardworking individual with a high attention to detail  </li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent organization skills </li>\r\n                                <li>3+ years of hospital auditing/coding experience with CPT, ICD, HCPCS and modifier coding </li>\r\n                                <li>Experience working within the hospital environment preferred </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p><b>Education/Certification:</b></p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>CPC, RHIT, RHIA, or other coding/clinical certifications, credentials, or expertise preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>Must pass Certified Revenue Cycle Representative (CRCR) within 90 days of employment</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Nurse Auditor-Charge Description Master (CDM)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nurse-auditor-charge-description-master-cdm', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:54:13', '2017-10-07 06:54:13', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=334', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(335, 1, '2017-10-07 06:54:37', '2017-10-07 06:54:37', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for leaders with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Manager, Billing Services will support the Director of Revenue Cycle in the selection, direction and development of billing department team members, and will report to the Director of Revenue Cycle. The Manager will be responsible for assisting Team members with problematic bills and questions regarding billing processes. The Manager will be responsible to report on Key Performance Indicators for the department and will be held to the standards identified as benchmarks for each client. Position duties include managing the daily work-flow of the department, monitoring progress to identify trending issues and develop training or processes to address these issues. The Manager will also hold huddles to efficiently cover new or evolving training focuses to encourage and develop team members. The Manager will be responsible for overseeing progress on the floor and monitoring the worked accounts for quality assurance.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Leadership within Ensemble work for our team members and our clients. While there is a lot of responsibility within the leadership role, there is also an opportunity to influence, guide and encourage the team members you work for.  As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place leaders in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates that exemplify the following traits would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>3-5 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance Claims and working knowledge of healthcare Revenue Cycle required, hospital specific insurance experience required</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Finance, Business, Accounting or a Healthcare specific field required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal skills and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Leadership skills ‚Äì the ability to motivate and lead in a team-based productivity environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Resourcefulness, Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>A Player that has insight into associates and accounts, shows exceptional intelligence and has the ability to motivate teams</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Manager, Billing Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'manager-billing-services', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:54:37', '2017-10-07 06:54:37', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=335', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(336, 1, '2017-10-07 06:55:56', '2017-10-07 06:55:56', ' <p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Insurance Reimbursement Specialist position is a general role that will ultimately branch into more specialized roles depending the individual strengths and areas of expertise presented by each selected team member. The Insurance Reimbursement Specialist is responsible for contacting the insurance carrier specific to their assigned account queue and following up on the under-paid claims, to result in payment on the account. The Specialist will review account specifics to evaluate how to follow-up with the Insurance payer on the aged or delayed Claims, and be responsible for contacting them by phone to move the account forward in the payment process. Following the conversations, the Specialist will note all accounts appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place team members in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths. We will be looking for candidates with background in Insurance follow-up, insurance collections and reviewing patient accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates who feel that they fit the following would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>1-3 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance Claims and working knowledge of Healthcare Revenue Cycle required, hospital specific insurance experience preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>Associates degree preferred, High school Diploma or equivalent required</li>\r\n                                <li>Working knowledge of CPT/HCPCS codes</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>Comfortable with being on the phone with various parties for the greatest part of the day &ndash; capable of creating a professional and competent presence over the phone</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Insurance Reimbursement Specialist', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'insurance-reimbursement-specialist', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:55:56', '2017-10-07 06:55:56', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=336', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(337, 1, '2017-10-07 06:56:25', '2017-10-07 06:56:25', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers who are well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for a leader with a background in information systems and technology, with a strong understanding of healthcare security system infrastructure, who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Information Technology Director will manage the Information Technology department, including the selection, direction and development of department team members and achievement of department objectives through the resources available. Daily responsibilities will include the management and analysis of information technology and maintenance of the integrity of company systems. General expectations of the position require that the Director provide oversight for the development and architecture of company IT infrastructure in correlation with the growth and needs of the organization, have a complete understanding of securely linking with client systems and an interdisciplinary understanding of database administration. Position duties include managing the daily workflow of the department, monitoring progress to identify trending issues and developing training or processes to address these issues. The Director will be responsible for ensuring consistent security of client and company electronic information and communication, in accordance with company policy and compliance.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Leadership within Ensemble work for our team members and clients. While there is a lot of responsibility within the leadership role, there is also an opportunity to influence, guide and encourage the team members you work for. As a company, our goal is to collectively succeed. As such, we hope to place leaders in an area that interests them and plays to their strengths.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates that exemplify the following traits would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>5+ years of experience working in management of Information Systems required, preferably within a healthcare industry or hospital environment</li>\r\n                                <li>2-4 years of previous supervisory experience, preferably within the healthcare setting, required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent working knowledge of security applications. Specific experience with Meraki systems preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>Experience with Active Directory functions and establishment and maintenance of VPNs site-to-site access</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor''s degree in Information Technology or equivalent discipline required. Master''s degree or equivalent experience or certification preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>Advanced communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Proven leadership skills&mdash;the ability to motivate and lead a team</li>\r\n                                <li>Resourcefulness, problem-solving and critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An internal drive to succeed and have pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Information Technology Director', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'information-technology-director', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:56:25', '2017-10-07 06:56:25', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=337', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(338, 1, '2017-10-07 06:56:47', '2017-10-07 06:56:47', '<p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for a leader with a background in Human Resources with experience in the healthcare environment, who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Human Resource Manager will be responsible for the identification, onboarding and development of Ensemble‚Äôs remote associate population. This will include communication regarding company policies, the administration of benefits, the completion of pre-employment requirements, and the appropriation of the associate file. The manager will report to the VP, Human Resources and will support the Human Resources department and staff. Other duties include orientation of new associates, management of employee relations concerns for the remote associate population, managing worker‚Äôs compensation and light duty requirements, and performing file audits. The Manager may be required to travel on an intermittent basis as business needs require.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Leadership within Ensemble work for our team members and our clients. While there is a lot of responsibility within the leadership role, there is also an opportunity to influence, guide and encourage the team members you work for.  As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place leaders in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates that exemplify the following traits would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>5+ years experience in Healthcare Human Resources role. Experience with Joint Commission requirement preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>2 - 4 years of previous supervisory experience, within the healthcare setting, required</li>\r\n                                <li>Bachelor''s degree in Human Resource Management or a related field required</li>\r\n                                <li>Current certification, PHR, SPHR, SHRM-CP or SHRM-SCP required</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent verbal skills and written communication skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Proven leadership skills ‚Äì the ability to motivate and lead in a team-based productivity environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Resourcefulness, problem solving and critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Human Resources Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'human-resources-manager', '', '', '2017-10-07 06:56:47', '2017-10-07 06:56:47', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=338', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(339, 1, '2017-10-07 07:00:46', '2017-10-07 07:00:46', ' <p>One of the foundations for our success and pillars of our <a href="culture.php">culture</a> at Ensemble Health Partners, is our commitment to providing real-time data and metrics to not only monitor our performance but to be able to provide <a href="benefits.php">corresponding reward for excellence</a>. The Financial Analyst plays a key role in making this possible.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The analyst will be responsible for:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Assisting senior leadership with reporting functions including the preparation, modification and development of selected recurring and ad-hoc revenue cycle and payer contracting reports</li>\r\n                                <li>Preparing daily, weekly, and monthly general and standard reporting, including productivity, metric performance, collections, comparative reports, account Reconciliation of reports, presentations and invoices</li>\r\n                                <li>Maintaining and reviewing benchmark data</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place team members in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths. We will be looking for a team member with background in analytic roles, a true understanding of the value that accurate, up-to-the-minute, reporting provides, and a passion to problem solve. We love team members that love numbers, and candidates who love numbers and want a role that makes a huge contribution to the team, will love this position.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates who feel that they fit the following would enjoy the financial analyst opportunity:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>Bachelors Degree with emphasis in business, healthcare, and/or accounting, required.</li>\r\n                                <li>3-5 years experience in an analytical role, preferably in healthcare, required.</li>\r\n                                <li>Strong Excel skills, working knowledge of formula usage</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent attention to detail</li>\r\n                                <li>Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Financial Analyst', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'financial-analyst', '', '', '2017-10-07 07:00:46', '2017-10-07 07:00:46', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=339', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(340, 1, '2017-10-07 07:01:27', '2017-10-07 07:01:27', ' <p>Ensemble Health Partners is looking to build a team of top performers well versed in the Healthcare Revenue Cycle and eager to meet and exceed client expectations. We are searching for team members with a background in the revenue cycle from either the Healthcare providers or payers perspective who would like to maximize their professional potential.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>The Billing Specialist position is responsible for using coding data to prepare and submit clean claims to various insurance companies electronically or by paper. The Specialist will review and work daily reports to ensure claims have been properly billed, to result in payment on the account. Following any action taken, the Specialist will note all accounts appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>As a company our goal is to collectively succeed. As such we hope to place team members in an area that interests them and that plays to their strengths. We will be looking for candidates with background in billing, claim rejections and edits.</p>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Candidates who feel that they fit the following would enjoy this position:</p>\r\n\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>1-3 years experience working with Healthcare Insurance Claims and working knowledge of Healthcare Revenue Cycle required, hospital specific insurance experience preferred</li>\r\n                                <li>Associates degree preferred, High school Diploma or equivalent required</li>\r\n                                <li>Working knowledge of CPT/HCPCS codes</li>\r\n                                <li>Excellent attention to detail</li>\r\n                                <li>Problem Solving and Critical thinking skills</li>\r\n                                <li>Adaptability to rapid growth and a progressing environment</li>\r\n                                <li>Integrity and Honesty</li>\r\n                                <li>An Internal Drive to Succeed and pride in accomplishments</li>\r\n                                <li>High degree of professionalism and customer service</li>\r\n                                <li>Comfortable with being on the phone with various parties for the greatest part of the day &ndash; capable of creating a professional and competent presence over the phone</li>\r\n                                <li>Ability to pass the Certified Revenue Cycle Representative examination offered through the Healthcare Financial Management Association within 90 days of hire</li>\r\n                                <li>SSI experience preferred</li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n\r\n                            <p>Ensemble Health Partners is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.</p>', 'Billing Specialist', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'billing-specialist', '', '', '2017-10-07 07:01:27', '2017-10-07 07:01:27', '', 0, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//?post_type=opportunities&#038;p=340', 0, 'opportunities', '', 0),
(341, 1, '2017-10-07 07:18:53', '2017-10-07 07:18:53', '<h1 class="cushycms" title="Main Header">Ensemble Careers</h1>\r\n\r\n                    <p class="emphasized cushycms" title="Description">Ensemble Health Partners is dedicated to providing our clients with experienced healthcare finance and revenue cycle professionals. We believe that our core values of trust, integrity, loyalty and service married with the belief that our work is worthwhile helps us build and sustain sincere relationships with our associates and clients. If you are a passionate, dedicated and experienced revenue cycle, consulting or finance professional and seek career and personal growth, we would love to hear from you. We believe we foster an environment where talented individuals can excel and shine. Our team believes that people are the most important part of our success and that when we take care of our people, they pay it forward by providing our clients with excellent results and world-class service.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <h2 class="cushycms" title="Secondary Header">How do I apply and what should I expect?</h2>\r\n\r\n                    <p class="emphasized cushycms" title="Description">You can apply by <a href="https://ts.tgsnapshot.com/signup.cfm?DL=3858" target="_blank">clicking here</a>, find out more by attending one of our <a href="http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//events/">Open House/Career Fairs</a> or read more about our open positions below and apply directly.<br />\r\n                        <br />\r\n                        Through the interview process, you will have the opportunity to speak with multiple members of management, be given plenty of time to discuss your passion and career goals and ultimately to connect future managers to your previous managers through our reference program. We apply Topgrading principles in our <a href="culture.php#process">hiring process</a> because we believe every new team member is worth taking the time to get to know. By the time you hit the floor, we''d like you to know enough about us that you are as excited as we are about the opportunities available within Ensemble.<br />\r\n                    </p>\r\n[opurtunities-list]', 'Careers', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-07 07:18:53', '2017-10-07 07:18:53', '', 24, 'http://greenpagebd.com/ensemble//24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
